1 
;The yeast mitochondrial cytochrome bc1 complex consist of 9 subunits (COR1, QCR2, COB, CYT1, RIP1, QCR6, QCR7, QCR8, QCR9). The biological functional unit is a homodimer. The smallest subunit QCR10, which is not required for a functional enzyme, was not present in the protein preparations.
;
? 
2 
;The cytochrome bc1 complex was co-crystallized with an antibody Fv-fragment, which is bound to subunit RIP1 ("Rieske"-protein). The Fv-fragment consists of heavy and light chain (VH and VL). the Fv-fragment is bound to the "Rieske"-protein (chain ID E)
;
? 
